<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1903-06-06T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1903-06-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="59" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d59">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Conger</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-06-06"><hi rend="italic">June 6,
                                1903</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Replying to Mr. Conger’s telegram of June 6, Mr. Hay instructs him to
                            take no action on matter until further instructed, as it is being
                            discussed in Washington by the Russian ambassador under instructions
                            from his Government.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>